# 2p_ctf_combat — host (RED) shoots client (BLUE) on a CTF map.
#
# This is the regression test for the "shooting opposing mechs in
# CTF mode does nothing" bug — the auto-balance had been running
# AFTER lobby_spawn_round_mechs, so both players ended up on RED
# (FFA-default) and friendly_fire=off blocked all damage.
#
# Verifies on the host log: hit events fire (mech_apply_damage gets
# past the friendly-fire gate), the victim takes damage, and
# eventually dies. Pairs with 2p_ctf_combat.client.shot which is
# stationary fodder.
#
# Crossfire is huge (4480 px wide) so we use spawn_at + peer_spawn
# to put both players in close range. Pulse Rifle range is 2400 px
# but moving the test to ~200 px apart keeps tracers tight.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/host_ctf_combat
network host 24028
name HostRed

# Both bodies on a flat strip near red base. Host (slot 0) at left,
# client (slot 1) just to the right within rifle range.
spawn_at 2200 1100
peer_spawn 1 2400 1100

# Aim at the client's chest.
aim 2400 1070

contact_sheet sheet cols 4 cell 320 180

# Phase 1 (100-180): settle, take stock.
at 100 shot t100_spawn

# Phase 2 (180+): hold fire on the client. Pulse Rifle 18 dmg / 110ms,
# 150 HP target → ~9 hits to drop = ~1 second on full-auto.
at 180 press fire
at 360 release fire

at 250 shot t250_trading
at 380 shot t380_post_kill

at 600 end
